%N A394451 Decimal expansion of the area of a 20-gon with unit side lengths.
%C A394451 The largest solution to x^4 - 20*x^3 - 350*x^2 - 500*x + 625 = 0.
%C A394451 This constant multiplied by the square of the side length of a regular 20-gon equals the area of that 20-gon.
%C A394451 20^2 divided by this constant equals 80 * tan(Pi/20) = 12.67075522... which is the perimeter and the area of an equable 20-gon with its side length 4 * tan(Pi/20) = 0.63353776... .
%H A394451 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Icosagon">Icosagon</a>.
%F A394451 Equals 5 / tan(Pi/20).
%F A394451 Equals 5 / (1 + sqrt(5) - sqrt(5 + sqrt(20))).
%F A394451 Equals 5 * tan(9*Pi/20).
%F A394451 Equals 5 * (1 + sqrt(5) + sqrt(5 + sqrt(20))).
%F A394451 Equals 5 + 10 * (sqrt(5/4) + sqrt(5/4 + sqrt(5/4))) = 5 + 10 * A188594.
%F A394451 Equals 5 * phi * (2 + sqrt(5/2 + sqrt(5/4))) where phi = 1.61803398... .
%e A394451 31.5687575733752154...
%p A394451 evalf((5 / tan(Pi/20)), 105);
%t A394451 RealDigits[5 / Tan[Pi/20], 10, 105][[1]]
%o A394451 (PARI) 5 / tan(Pi/20)
%Y A394451 Cf. A001622, A019907, A019979, A188594.
%K A394451 nonn,cons,new
%O A394451 2,1
